Barbosa, Nessimian &amp; Ferreira-Keppler.
</taxonomicName>
13, Lateral view of male rostrum with rostral prong shorter than third rostral segment; 14, Ventral view of male fore leg without stridulatory area on femur and dissimilar stridulatory teeth on tibia; 15, Dorsal view of fore leg with internal margin of tibia bluntly projected; 16, Mid-tibia with lateral expansion near the base of lateral margin; 17, Claspers. Scale bar: 0.5 mm. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1081,1151,1771,1793]" pageId="7" pageNumber="108">18–20.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authority="Barbosa, Nessimian &amp; Ferreira-Keppler." authorityName="Barbosa, Nessimian &amp; Ferreira-Keppler." class="Insecta" family="Notonectidae" genus="Buenoa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="108" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="exilidens">
<emphasis box="[1160,1337,1771,1793]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="108">Buenoa exilidens</emphasis>
Barbosa, Nessimian &amp; Ferreira-Keppler.
</taxonomicName>
18, Lateral view of male rostrum with rostral prong distinctly longer than third rostral segment; 19, Ventral view of male fore leg with stridulatory area on femur and similar stridulatory teeth on tibia; 20, Claspers. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1366,1436,1832,1854]" pageId="7" pageNumber="108">21–22.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authority="Fieber" authorityName="Fieber" box="[151,421,1863,1885]" class="Insecta" family="Notonectidae" genus="Buenoa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="108" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="femoralis">
<emphasis box="[151,330,1863,1885]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="108">Buenoa femoralis</emphasis>
(Fieber)
</taxonomicName>
. 21, Lateral view of male rostrum with rostral prong distinctly longer than third rostral segment; 22, Ventral view of male fore leg with stridulatory area on femur and similar stridulatory teeth on tibia. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1162,1232,1893,1915]" pageId="7" pageNumber="108">23–26.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authority="Berg" authorityName="Berg" class="Insecta" family="Notonectidae" genus="Buenoa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="108" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="fuscipennis">
<emphasis box="[1238,1436,1893,1916]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="108">Buenoa fuscipennis</emphasis>
(Berg)
</taxonomicName>
. 23, Lateral view of male rostrum with rostral prong distinctly shorter than third rostral segment; 24, Ventral view of male fore leg with a tubercle on trochanter, without stridulatory area on femur and similar stridulatory teeth on tibia; 25, Midtibia with internal margin dilated; 26, Claspers.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph blockId="8.[151,1436,151,431]" pageId="8" pageNumber="109">
These differences can be populational variations, because the described specimens in Truxal’s revision are from 
<collectingCountry box="[215,270,192,215]" name="Peru" pageId="8" pageNumber="109">Peru</collectingCountry>
. In the original description, Fieber (
<number box="[686,744,190,215]" pageId="8" pageNumber="109" value="1851.0">1851</number>
) described specimens from 
<collectingCountry box="[1069,1205,190,215]" name="Puerto Rico" pageId="8" pageNumber="109">Puerto Rico</collectingCountry>
with “ 
<number box="[1285,1300,191,215]" pageId="8" pageNumber="109" value="4.0">4</number>
Linien 
<number box="[1383,1391,187,201]" pageId="8" pageNumber="109" value="8.0">8</number>
” of length; Barber (
<number box="[329,389,227,251]" pageId="8" pageNumber="109" value="1939.0">1939</number>
), from 
<collectingCountry box="[473,607,226,251]" name="Puerto Rico" pageId="8" pageNumber="109">Puerto Rico</collectingCountry>
and 
<collectingCountry box="[664,825,226,251]" name="Virgin Islands" pageId="8" pageNumber="109">Virgin Islands</collectingCountry>
, with 8.00 to 
<quantity box="[982,1086,226,251]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="8.5" pageId="8" pageNumber="109" unit="mm" value="8.5">8.50 mm</quantity>
. Relations between the lengths are similar to those described by Truxal. On the other hand, material observed by Jaczewski (
<number box="[1209,1269,263,287]" pageId="8" pageNumber="109" value="1928.0">1928</number>
), from Paraná, has a synthlipsis with width slightly wider than one-third of the anterior length of the vertex and a body length of 
<quantity box="[151,338,334,359]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="7.5" metricValueMax="7.75" metricValueMin="7.25" pageId="8" pageNumber="109" unit="mm" value="7.5" valueMax="7.75" valueMin="7.25">7.25 to 7.75 mm</quantity>
, similar to that observed in the specimen from Manaus.
</paragraph>
